# Cursor Rules — Secure Dual-Bank Bootloader

## Project context
This is a portfolio-grade ARM Cortex-M4 (STM32F407) secure bootloader with
ECDSA-P256 firmware verification, dual-bank A/B partitions, automatic
rollback, IWDG watchdog, and UART-based OTA updates. It is intended to
compile cleanly with `arm-none-eabi-gcc` and run in QEMU
(`-machine netduino2`) or Renode (`stm32f4_discovery`).

## Coding rules
- C11, freestanding, no libc allocation. Avoid `malloc`/`free`.
- All code must compile with `-Wall -Wextra -Werror`.
- Bootloader code must fit within 64 KB at 0x08000000-0x0800FFFF.
- Never modify the active firmware in place; write new firmware to the
  inactive slot only.
- All flash writes must use the `flash_driver` HAL, never direct memory
  writes (except inside the `QEMU_FLASH_SIM` short-circuit).
- All long-running loops (flash erase, OTA receive, ECDSA verify) must
  call `iwdg_kick()` periodically.
- Power-loss safety: write-then-readback-verify; the CRC field of any
  persisted record is written last so torn writes are detectable.

## Memory map (do not change without updating common/memory_map.h asserts)
- Bootloader:  0x08000000  (64 KB)
- BootConfig:  0x08010000  (4 KB logical, sector 4 on real F407)
- Slot A:      0x08011000  (460 KB)  -> app entry at 0x08011200
- Slot B:      0x08084000  (460 KB)  -> app entry at 0x08084200
- SharedBootBlock at 0x2001FFF0 in SRAM (16 B, NOLOAD)

## Crypto
- micro-ecc (SECP256R1) is the on-device verifier.
- Signature format: raw r||s, 64 bytes, big-endian, fixed-length.
- SHA-256 is computed over [header_with_zeroed_signature || payload].
- Public key is embedded as `public_key_xy[64]` (X || Y).

## Build conventions
- `make qemu`: Cortex-M3 / soft-float / `QEMU_FLASH_SIM=1`.
- `make hw`:   Cortex-M4 / hard-float / FPU / real FLASH register code.

## Style
- Doxygen-style comments on public functions in headers.
- No code comments that just narrate what the next line does. Comments
  explain why, not what.
- Use `static` for any function not exported in a header.
